<head>PCT 06: How Sweet-Grass Became Chief</head>
<docauthor>Coming-Day</docauthor>

<p n="1">

<seg n="1.1">
<w canon="kayâs" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="long_ago" stem="kayâs">kayâs</w>
<w canon="mitoni" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="intensively" stem="mitoni">mitonih</w>
<w canon="kisêyiniw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="old_man" stem="kisêyiniw" suffix="0">kisêyiniw</w>
<w canon="êwako" class="pr" gcat="PR" sgloss="that_one" stem="êwako">êwakôw</w>
<w canon="okimâw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="chief" stem="okimâw" suffix="0">okimâw</w>
.
<gloss>In the time of the men of long ago he was chief.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.2">
<w canon="ôma" class="dem" gcat="0sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="ôma">ôma</w>
<w canon="nakîwacîhk" class="ni" gcat="0locNI" sgloss="Sweet_Grass" stem="nakîwaciy" suffix="-ihk">nakîwacîhk</w>
<w canon="ôta" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="here" stem="ôta">ôtah</w>
<w canon="wîkiwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="live_there" stem="wîki" suffix="-wak">wîkiwak</w>
.
<gloss>Here at  Sweet-Grass they dwelt.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.3">
<w canon="kîtahtawê" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="at_times" stem="kêtahtawê">kîtahtawê</w>
<w canon="kîkisêpâ" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="early_in_morning" stem="kêkisêpâ">kîkisêpâ</w>
<w canon="otinêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="take" stem="otin" suffix="-êw">otnêw</w>
<w canon="misatimwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="horse" stem="mistatimw" suffix="-a">misatimwah</w>
;
<w canon="oyahpitêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="harness" stem="wiyahpit" suffix="-êw">oyahpitêw</w>
,
<w canon="ê-têhtapit" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_mounted" stem="têhtapi" suffix="-t">êh-têhtapit</w>
;
<w canon="sipwêhtêw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="leave" stem="sipwêhtê" suffix="-w">sipwêhtêw</w>
,
<w canon="ê-papâmohtêt" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="walk_about" stem="papâmohtê" suffix="-t">êh-papâmohtêt</w>
.
<gloss>One morning, he took a horse; he saddled it  and mounted; he set out to roam.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.4">
<w canon="mêkwâ" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="while" stem="mêkwâc">mêkwâ</w>
<w canon="ê-pimohtêt" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="go_along" stem="pimohtê" suffix="-t">êh-pimohtêt</w>
,
<w canon="ispatinâw" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="hill" stem="ispatinâw" suffix="0">ipatinâw</w>
<w canon="wâpahtam" class="vti" gcat="3sTI" sgloss="see" stem="wâpaht" suffix="-am">wâpahtam</w>
,
<w canon="ê-âmaciwêyit" class="vai" gcat="3oAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="go_uphill" stem="âmaciwê" suffix="-yit">êh-âmaciwêyit</w>
<w canon="ayîsiyiniwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="person" stem="ayisiyiniw" suffix="-a">ayîsiyiniwah</w>
,
<w canon="nâpêwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="man" stem="nâpêw" suffix="-a">nâpêwah</w>
.
<gloss>As he went along he saw someone climbing a hill, a man. He observed him, watching through a spy-glass,  this man who was looking for people.</gloss>
<note>?? ispatinâw ‘hill’?</note>
</seg>

<seg n="1.5">
<w canon="kiskêyimêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="know" stem="kiskêyim" suffix="-êw">kiskêyimêw</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="-a">ayâhciyiniwah</w>
.
<gloss>He knew him for a Blackfoot.</gloss>
<note>LB on {ayâhciyiniwah}:  In earlier texts I have noted the second vowel of this word as long;  later I heard it as predominantly short.</note>
</seg>

<seg n="1.6">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="opâskisikan" class="ni" gcat="0sNIof3s" prefix="3" sgloss="gun" stem="pâskisikan" suffix="0">opâskisikan</w>
<w canon="pîhtâsôw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="load_gun" stem="pîhtâso" suffix="-w">pîhtâsôw</w>
;
<w canon="môskîstawêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="attack" stem="môskîstaw" suffix="-êw">môskîstawêw</w>
<w canon="ê-pimisiniyit" class="vai" gcat="3oAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="lie_extended" stem="pimisin" suffix="-yit">êh-pimisiniyit</w>
.
<gloss>He loaded his gun and attacked him as he lay on the ground.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.7">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="ê-kî-kiskêyihtahk" class="vti" gcat="3sTIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj kî|PAST" sgloss="know" stem="kiskêyiht" suffix="-ahk">êh-kîh-kiskêyihtahk</w>
<w canon="awa" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa">aw</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="0">ayâhciyiniw</w>
,
<w canon="nêhiyawa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="Cree" stem="nêhiyaw" suffix="-a">nêhiyawah</w>
<w canon="ê-môskîstâkot" class="vta" gcat="3o3sTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="attack" stem="môskîstaw" suffix="-ikot">ê-môskîstâkot</w>
,
<w canon="tapasîw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="flee" stem="tapasî" suffix="-w">tapasîw</w>
;
<gloss>When the Blackfoot perceived that a Cree was attacking him, he fled;</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.8">
<w canon="ê-sakâyik" class="vii" gcat="0oIIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_bush" stem="sakâ" suffix="-yik">ê-sakâyik</w>
<w canon="kotêskâmôw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="flee_to_shelter" stem="kotêskâmo" suffix="-w">kotêskamôw</w>
.
<gloss>he hid in the bushes.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.9">
<w canon="êkosi" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thus" stem="êkosi">êkosi</w>
<w canon="pâskiswêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="shoot_at" stem="pâskisw" suffix="-êw">pâskiswêw</w>
<w canon="nêhiyaw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Cree" stem="nêhiyaw" suffix="0">nêhiyaw</w>
.
<gloss>The Cree tried to shoot him,</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.10">
<w canon="namôya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="namôya">namoya</w>
<w canon="matwêwêw" class="vii" gcat="0sII" sgloss="be_gunshot" stem="matwêwê" suffix="-w">matwêwiw</w>
<w canon="pâskisikan" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="gun" stem="pâskisikan" suffix="0">pâskisikan</w>
.
<gloss>but the gun did not go off.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.11">
<w canon="êkota" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="there" stem="êkota">êkotah</w>
<w canon="ê-sêskâmot" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="flee_into_bushes" stem="sêskâmo" suffix="-t">ê-sêskâmot</w>
,
<w canon="êkota" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="there" stem="êkota">êkotaw</w>
<w canon="ohci" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="thence" stem="ohci">ohci</w>
<w canon="matâwisiwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="move_into_open" stem="matâwisi" suffix="-wak">mâtâwisiwak</w>
<w canon="nîsosâp" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="twelve" stem="nîsosâp">nîsosâp</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniwak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="-ak">iyâhciyiniwak</w>
.
<gloss>From the place where he had fled into the woods, twelve Blackfoot came out upon the trail.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.12">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="nêhiyaw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Cree" stem="nêhiyaw" suffix="0">nêhiyaw</w>
<w canon="ê-pêyakot" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_alone" stem="pêyako" suffix="-t">êh-pêyakot</w>
<w canon="môskîstawêw" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTA" sgloss="attack" stem="môskîstaw" suffix="-êw">môskîstawêw</w>
,
<w canon="ê-wî-nôtinât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj wî|will" sgloss="fight" stem="nôtin" suffix="-ât">ê-wîh-nôtinât</w>
,
<w canon="ê-wî-pâskiswât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj wî|will" sgloss="shoot_at" stem="pâskisw" suffix="-ât">a-wîh-pâskiswât</w>
.
<gloss>The lone Cree attacked them, wanting to do battle and shoot them.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.13">
<w canon="tapasîwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="flee" stem="tapasî" suffix="-wak">tapasîwak</w>
<w canon="ôki" class="dem" gcat="3pDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa" suffix="-3p">ôki</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniwak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="-ak">iyâhciyiniwak</w>
,
<w canon="ê-pêyakoyit" class="vai" gcat="3oAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_alone" stem="pêyako" suffix="-yit">êh-pêyakowit</w>
<w canon="ê-kostâcik" class="vta" gcat="3p3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="fear" stem="kost" suffix="-âcik">êh-kostâcik</w>
,
<w canon="ê-pâh-pâskisokocik" class="vta" gcat="3o3pTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj dupH|H.REDUP" sgloss="shoot_at" stem="pâskisw" suffix="-ikocik">êh-pâh-pâskisokocik</w>
.
<gloss>The Blackfoot  fled, fearing the one Cree who was shooting at them.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.14">
<w canon="kotak" class="pr" gcat="0sPR" sgloss="other" stem="kotak">kotak</w>
<w canon="sakâw" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="bush" stem="sakâw" suffix="0">sakâw</w>
<w canon="êkota" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="there" stem="êkota">êkotah</w>
<w canon="mîna" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="also" stem="mîna">mînah</w>
<w canon="sêskâmôwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="flee_into_bushes" stem="sêskâmo" suffix="-wak">sêskâmôwak</w>
.
<gloss>They fled into another wood.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.15">
<w canon="âsay" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="already" stem="âsay">âsay</w>
<w canon="mîna" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="also" stem="mîna">mînah</w>
<w canon="matâwisiwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="move_into_open" stem="matâwisi" suffix="-wak">mâtâwisiwak</w>
,
<w canon="ê-pimipahtâcik" class="vai" gcat="3pAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="run" stem="pimipahtâ" suffix="-cik">êh-pimipahtâcik</w>
.
<gloss>Again they came forth in their course.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.16">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="awa" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa">awa</w>
<w canon="nêhiyaw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Cree" stem="nêhiyaw" suffix="0">nêhiyaw</w>
<w canon="ê-têhtapit" class="vai" gcat="3sAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_mounted" stem="têhtapi" suffix="-t">êh-têhtapit</w>
,
<w canon="êkotê" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="over_there" stem="êkotê">êkotê</w>
<w canon="mîkiwâhpa" class="ni" gcat="0pNI" sgloss="lodge" stem="mîkiwâhp" suffix="-a">mîkiwâhpah</w>
,
<w canon="mitoni" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="intensively" stem="mitoni">miton</w>
<w canon="ê-mihcêticik" class="vai" gcat="3pAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_numerous" stem="mihcêti" suffix="-cik">ê-mihcêticik</w>
<w canon="nêhiyawak" class="na" gcat="3pNA" sgloss="Cree" stem="nêhiyaw" suffix="-ak">nêhiyawak</w>
,
<w canon="êkotê" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="over_there" stem="êkotê">êkotê</w>
<w canon="ê-itisahwât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="send" stem="itisahw" suffix="-ât">êh-itisahwât</w>
.
<gloss>But the Cree on his horse was driving them to where the Cree were many in their tents.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.17">
<w canon="ayahciyiniw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="0">iyâhciyiniw</w>
<q>
<w canon="êkotê" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="over_there" stem="êkotê">êkotê</w>
<w canon="nika-pimâtisin" class="vai" gcat="1sAI" prefix="1" preverbs="ka|will" sgloss="live" stem="pimâtisi" suffix="-n">nika-pimâtisin</w>
</q>,
<w canon="ê-itêyihtahk" class="vti" gcat="3sTIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="think_of" stem="itêyiht" suffix="-ahk">êh-itêyihtahk</w>
,
<w canon="namôya" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="not" stem="namôya">namoya</w>
<w canon="kiskêyihtam" class="vti" gcat="3sTI" sgloss="know" stem="kiskêyiht" suffix="-am">kiskêyihtam</w>
<w canon="ayîsiyiniwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="person" stem="ayisiyiniw" suffix="-a">ayîsiyiniwah</w>
<w canon="nêhiyawa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="Cree" stem="nêhiyaw" suffix="-a">nêhiyawah</w>
<w canon="ê-mihcêtiyit" class="vai" gcat="3oAIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_numerous" stem="mihcêti" suffix="-yit">ê-mihcêtiyit</w>
<w canon="êkota" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="there" stem="êkota">êkotah</w>
<w canon="kâ-itohtêcik" class="vai" gcat="3pAIcnj" preverbs="kâ|cnj" sgloss="go" stem="itohtê" suffix="-cik">k-êtohtêcik</w>
.
<gloss>The Blackfoot meanwhile, thinking, “In this direction  I shall escape,” did not know that there were many people, many Cree in the place to which they were going.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="1.18">
<w canon="iyikohk" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="so_much" stem="iyikohk">iyikohk</w>
<w canon="ê-wâpamâcik" class="vta" gcat="3p3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="see" stem="wâpam" suffix="-âcik">êh-wâpamâcik</w>
<w canon="nêhiyawa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="Cree" stem="nêhiyaw" suffix="-a">nêhiyawah</w>
,
<w canon="êkoyikohk" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="that_much" stem="êkoyikohk">êkoyikohk</w>
<w canon="wâyonîwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="turn_back" stem="wâwonî" suffix="-wak">wayoniwak</w>
,
<w canon="ê-kî-wâpamâcik" class="vta" gcat="3p3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj kî|PAST" sgloss="see" stem="wâpam" suffix="-âcik">êh-kîh-wâpamâcik</w>
<w canon="mihcêt" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="many" stem="mihcêt">mihcêt</w>
<w canon="nêhiyawa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="Cree" stem="nêhiyaw" suffix="-a">nêhiyawah</w>
.
<gloss>When they saw the Cree, they turned, at the sight of the many Cree.</gloss>
</seg>
</p>

<p n="2">

<seg n="2.1">
<w canon="êkwa" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="then" stem="êkwa">êkwah</w>
<w canon="pêyak" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="one" stem="pêyak">pêyak</w>
<w canon="awa" class="dem" gcat="3sDEM" sgloss="this" stem="awa">awah</w>
<w canon="nîsosâp" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="twelve" stem="nîsosâp">nîsosâp</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniwa" class="na" gcat="3oNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="-a">iyâhciyiniwah</w>
<w canon="ê-nawaswâtât" class="vta" gcat="3s3oTAcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="pursue" stem="nawaswât" suffix="-ât">êh-nawaswâtât</w>
,
<w canon="ê-sakâyik" class="vii" gcat="0oIIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="be_bush" stem="sakâ" suffix="-yik">ê-sakâyik</w>
<w canon="êyoko" class="pr" gcat="PR" sgloss="that_one" stem="êwako">êyakô</w>
<w canon="môskîstamwak" class="vti" gcat="3pTI" sgloss="attack" stem="môskîst" suffix="-amwak">môskîstamwak</w>
<w canon="sîpîsis" class="ni" gcat="0sNI" sgloss="small_river" stem="sîpîsis" suffix="0">sîpîsis</w>
.
<gloss>Then, as the one was pursuing the twelve Blackfoot, in a wooded place they made for a creek.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="2.2">
<w canon="êkota" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="there" stem="êkota">êkotah</w>
<w canon="pahkopêwak" class="vai" gcat="3pAI" sgloss="walk_into_water" stem="pahkopê" suffix="-wak">pahkopêwak</w>
,
<w canon="ê-âsôwahahkik" class="vti" gcat="3pTIcnj" preverbs="ê|cnj" sgloss="cross" stem="âsowah" suffix="-ahkik">êh-âsôwahahkik</w>
.
<gloss>They went into the water to cross.</gloss>
</seg>

<seg n="2.3">
<w canon="êkota" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="there" stem="êkota">êkotah</w>
<w canon="nipîhk" class="ni" gcat="0locNI" sgloss="water" stem="nipiy" suffix="-ihk">nipîhk</w>
<w canon="kôkîw" class="vai" gcat="3sAI" sgloss="dive" stem="kôkî" suffix="-w">kôkîw</w>
<w canon="pêyak" class="ipc" gcat="IPC" sgloss="one" stem="pêyak">pêyak</w>
<w canon="ayahciyiniw" class="na" gcat="3sNA" sgloss="Blackfoot" stem="ayahciyiniw" suffix="0">ayâhciyiniw</w>
,
